<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9623&amp;p=104980#p104980"><![CDATA[
I solved the problem using 100nF decoupling capacitors.<br /><br />Finally my board has not any pull-up, one 100nF ceramic capacitor for decoupling near each 27C322, another 100nF cap for SuperCIC, and one 22 uF electrolytic capacitor near Vcc to decouple noise in the whole board.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=875">magno</a> — Fri Dec 21, 2012 2:42 am</p><hr />
