<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9623&amp;p=104942#p104942</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9623&amp;p=104942#p104942"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: About capacitors on SNES boards]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9623&amp;p=104942#p104942"><![CDATA[
From looking at a few PCB scans, those capacitors are 10nF and 1nF (black/brown/yellow/x/x is 10nF, black/brown/orange/x/x is 1 nF).  Like I said, read the datasheets for your chips.  It differs per chip, but most SRAM chips I've seen have at least suggested smoothing caps.  As for the RESET line, thinking about it now, it definitely makes sense that the console would drive it rather than leaving it open, but for the /CE lines on the ROM and SRAM, I would definitely pull those up if you aren't already.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5348">qwertymodo</a> — Thu Dec 20, 2012 2:09 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
